{"title_page": "Keijo (manga)", "text_new": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Keijo!!!!!!!!\n| image           = Keijo!!!!!!!! volume 1 cover.jpg\n| alt             = The cover shows a group of women in bikinis; the character Nozomi is in the front, and twists, showing her buttocks to the viewer.\n| caption         = Cover of the first manga volume\n| ja_kanji        = \u7af6\u5973!!!!!!!!\n| genre           = [[Comedy]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Keijo!!!!!!!! |url=https://www.funimation.com/shows/keijo/ |publisher=Funimation |accessdate=June 18, 2018}}</ref> [[Sports manga|sports]]<ref name=end/><!-- Note: Use and cite reliable sources to identify genre/s, not personal interpretation. Please don't include more than three genres (per [[MOS:A&M]]). -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Daichi Sorayomi\n| publisher       = [[Shogakukan]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| imprint         = Sh\u014dnen Sunday Comics\n| magazine        = [[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Sunday]]\n| first           = July 24, 2013\n| last            = April 26, 2017\n| volumes         = 18\n| volume_list     = #Volume list\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = TV series \n| director        = Hideya Takahashi\n| producer        = Nobuhiro Nakayama<br>Jun Fukuda<br>Takatoshi Chino<br>Takeshi Okamura<br>Ry\u016btaro Usukura<br>Toshiyasu Hayashi<br>Atsushi Aitani\n| writer          = Takao Kato\n| music           = [[Hayato Matsuo]]\n| studio          = [[Xebec (studio)|Xebec]]\n| licensee        = [[Crunchyroll]]<br>[[Funimation]]\n| network         = [[Tokyo MX]], [[AT-X (company)|AT-X]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]]\n| network_en      = \n| first           = October 6, 2016\n| last            = December 22, 2016\n| episodes        = 12 + 6 OVA\n| episode_list    = #Episode list\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Keijo!!!!!!!!'''''|\u7af6\u5973!!!!!!!!|extra=lit. 'Competitive-girl'|lead=yes}}, also known as '''''Hip Whip Girl''''', is a Japanese sports [[manga]] series written and illustrated by Daichi Sorayomi. It was serialized in [[Shogakukan]]'s [[sh\u014dnen manga]] magazine ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Sunday]]'' from July 2013 to April 2017. It was collected into eighteen ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes. An [[anime]] adaptation ran from October 6 to December 22, 2016. The series centers around the fictional women-only sport of keijo, where players stand on floating platforms and aim to incapacitate or push opponents into the water, using only breasts and buttocks. It also follows Nozomi Kaminashi, a gymnast who trains at the school, hoping to become the richest player in Japan.\n\n==Premise==\nThe series is set in an alternate reality where a new, women-only, gambling sport known as \"keijo\", quickly becomes a fad in Japan since the introduction in the dawn of the 21st century. Keijo matches are held atop floating platforms, referred to as a \"Land\", in large water-filled stadiums where swimsuit-clad players fight to incapacitate their opponents or push them out to the water, but they can only hit each other using their breasts or buttocks.\n\nNozomi Kaminashi gives up her dream from competing the Olympics, becoming a keijo player and aiming for high earnings. As she enters the world of Keijo, Nozomi makes new friends and rivals, while learning that the way to fame and fortune in a new uncommon sport, having more challenges than she ever imagined.\n\n==Characters==\n;{{Nihongo|'''Nozomi Kaminashi'''|\u795e\u7121 \u306e\u305e\u307f|Kaminashi Nozomi}} \n:{{voiced by|[[Lynn (voice actress)|Lynn]]<ref name=\"ann premiere\"/>|[[Amber Lee Connors]]<ref name=\"dub cast\">{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-24/funimation-reveals-english-dub-cast-for-keijo-anime/.108053 |title=Funimation Reveals English Dub Cast for Keijo!!!!!!!! Anime |date=October 25, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |access-date=October 25, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025001230/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-24/funimation-reveals-english-dub-cast-for-keijo-anime/.108053 |archive-date=October 25, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n:An energetic and cheerful girl who aims to become the richest keijo player in Japan. As an Olympic gymnastics, Nozomi is very athletic, using her skills to quickly move around the Land with ease. Her fighting style is Infighter style, due to her raw power. Her signature attack is the Vacuum Butt Cannon, which can blow anyone and anything away which plays a major key in this series. In school, she can be a troublemaker, determined and is clever although she can get stuck in tough cases like wearing the UTM and pulling out turnips with her butt. Also, she has a strong hunch when she has her head in a girl's butt, so she can figure out what her opponent's special talent is. Despite her loss, she redeem herself by learning all she can from the school teachers, friends and the professionals.\n;{{Nihongo|'''Sayaka Miyata'''|\u5bae\u7530 \u3055\u3084\u304b|Miyata Sayaka}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Mao Ichimichi|M.A.O]]<ref name=\"ann premiere\"/>|[[Felecia Angelle]]<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>|}}\n:Nozomi's best friend and a former judo champion. She is fast and strong and is considered among the most promising new recruits. She later claims herself the fastest in Western Japan. Her fighting style is Outfighter in which she uses her speed combined with her skill. Even though she's not phased by her classmate's antics with exception to Nozomi, she's a caring friend to her roommates and problem solve issues her friends have.<ref name=\"episode 3\">episode 3</ref>\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Kazane Aoba'''|\u9752\u8449 \u98a8\u97f3|Aoba Kazane}} \n:{{Voiced by|[[Kaede Hondo]]<ref name=\"ann premiere\"/>|[[Alexis Tipton]]<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:A resident of [[Hiroshima]], who is initially quiet and soft-spoken, due to being self-conscious about her dialect until she finally speaks out in the final hip toss endurance test. Her ponytail moves in reaction when she is addressed or when she feels emotions. Her right hand is very sensitive and is able to determine and even copy her opponents abilities by feeling up their butts, an ability she calls Scanning Hand. In addition, she is a great strategist and is able to use special abilities from her friends as the situation demands in the East West War. The reading material she likes to read is the Keijo Magazines. Her fighting style is Counter. Lastly, out of the girl group that lives in room 309, she's the only one who wears the scarf around her neck.<ref name=\"episode 3\"/>\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Non Toyoguchi'''|\u8c4a\u53e3 \u306e\u3093|Toyoguchi Non}} \n:{{Voiced by|[[Saori \u014cnishi]]<ref name=\"ann premiere\"/>|[[Sarah Wiedenheft]]<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:A girl from a countryside village, who wishes to become a Keijo player in the hope that by gaining popularity, she can revitalize her village which is losing the population. She has the softest buttocks and breast which allows her to absorb attacks and reflect it back. She is also known to be very clumsy. Not only that, she can be absent minded and also goes into any comical situation like wearing Miyata's bra and panties, and wearing her entrance dress back to front. Not to mention she has an unusual accent along with Kazane which is why Nozomi doesn't understand her. But in the English version, their accents are more southern cowboy accent instead since it's hard to translate unusual Japanese accent into English in a coherent manner. Her fighting style is Counter.<ref name=\"episode 3\"/>\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Hanabi Kawai'''|\u6cb3\u5408 \u82b1\u706b|Kawai Hanabi}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Rena Maeda]]<ref name=\"ann premiere\"/>|Kristen McGuire<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:Is an Elite Class Rank 3. She is considered a sports prodigy ever since she was a child and because of this, she had no friends until she took up Keijo. She has a happy go lucky attitude when playing on the Land. Her attack strategy is to strike her opponent's jaw which causes a shock to their brain that knocks them out. A cross-like sparkle appears on her eyes whenever she is participating. Her attack style is Infighter.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Mio Kusakai'''|\u65e5\u4e0b\u751f \u7f8e\u685c|Kusakai Mio}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Hibiku Yamamura]]<ref name=\"ann premiere\"/>|[[Michelle Rojas]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.funimation.com/blog/2016/10/18/fall-2016-simuldub-english-cast-announcements-for-the-love-of-dubs/ |title=Fall 2016 SimulDub English Cast Announcements \u2013 For The Love of Dubs |date=October 18, 2016 |publisher=[[Funimation]] |access-date=October 27, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027060125/http://www.funimation.com/blog/2016/10/18/fall-2016-simuldub-english-cast-announcements-for-the-love-of-dubs/ |archive-date=October 27, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n:Is an Elite Class Rank 1. She is known to be a lesbian who flirts with other girls. She's a happy, playful character with a great interest in Nozomi. In addition to her great athleticism, she is also able to use a technique called Titty Hypnosis in which she sways her ample breasts like a pendulum which dazes and confounds her opponents though the technique has been banned in their school due to the potential of it causing inexperienced opponents to drown in their hypnotized state. Her fighting style is Infighter.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Rin Rokud\u014d'''|\u516d\u5802 \u9234|Rokud\u014d Rin}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Rie Takahashi]]<ref name=\"ann premiere\"/>|Alex Moore<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/plus3toogres/status/796374941922947072 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-11-10 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225193642/https://twitter.com/plus3toogres/status/796374941922947072 |archivedate=2017-12-25 }}</ref>}}\n:Is an Elite Class Rank 2. She is a former swimmer and initially claims the title of the fastest in Western Japan which sparks a rivalry between her and Sayaka. As a former swimmer, she has a greater lung capacity which allows her to continuously move at a great speed without losing her breath for periods of time. Her favorite technique is the Butt Gattling. Whenever she participates in Keijo, her hair would stand which and takes a form similar to cat ears. This, in addition to her small frame and cat-like expressions, caused her friends to give her the nickname Rinrin. Her fighting style is Outfighter.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Yuko \u014cshima'''|\u5927\u5cf6 \u512a\u5b50|\u014cshima Yuko}}\n:{{Voiced by|Misa Kayama|Kristen McGuire<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:She's the main teacher in the West. She gives out tasks for the girls that are related to Keijo. Like hip toss with the beach ball and giving morning exercise. She has amazing speed as a test in the second episode knocking all four students off the land.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Nagisa Ujibe'''|\u6c0f\u90e8 \u51ea|Ujibe Nagisa}}\n:{{Voiced by|Mabuki And\u014d|[[Jamie Marchi]]<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:One of the first Keijo players and prize queens known as the Alluring Siren in the past. In the present, she is now a teacher in the training school Nozomi and the others attend. She was the first to recognize Nozomi's Vacuum Butt Cannon move and knows the danger of the attack as she once used it herself. Also she own the UTMs which she gives to Nozomi before giving to her elite class in preparation for the East West War. She has a rivalry with the Keijo training school's head teacher in East.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Miku Kobayakawa'''|\u5c0f\u65e9\u5ddd \u672a\u6765|Kobayakawa Miku}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Y\u014dko Hikasa]]|Dawn M. Bennett<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:She's one of the other teacher's in the West. Although she looks blind, she's also a good Keijo teacher. She's able to hit Nozomi Kaminashi when she's not paying attention with a perfect butt hit with the chalk on her forehead.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Kotone Fujisaki'''|\u85e4\u5d0e \u7434\u97f3|Fujisaki Kotone}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Shizuka Ishigami]]|[[Jad Saxton]]}}\n:Is an Elite Class Rank 4. She comes from a family of Keijo players and is naturally gifted at the sport. However, she sees it as nothing more than work, until she meets Nozomi and participate in Keijo for the first time. She can attack while her back is turned and uses the vibrations on the Land to detect and predict her opponents' movements without looking. Her buttocks releases an aura that takes the form of a dog she calls Cerberus and her buttocks appear to be able to home in on her target as though she were moving on auto-pilot. When not participating in Keijo, she is always listening to homosexual stories on her headset and occasionally fantasizes about it which, to her opponents, makes it appear uninteresting. Her fighting style is Infighter.\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n''Keijo!!!!!!!!'' is written and illustrated by Daichi Sorayomi. It ran in [[Shogakukan]]'s [[sh\u014dnen manga|''sh\u014dnen'' manga]] magazine ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Sunday]]'' from July 24, 2013 to April 26, 2017,<ref>{{cite web |title=\u300c\u9280\u306e\u5319\u300d\u79d8\u8535\u8a2d\u5b9a\u96c6\u304c\u30b5\u30f3\u30c7\u30fc\u306b\u3001\u7a7a\u8a60\u5927\u667a\u65b0\u9023\u8f09\u3082 |url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/95638 |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |accessdate=April 27, 2019 |language=ja |date=July 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u300c\u7af6\u5973!!!!!!!!\u300d\u7d42\u5c3b\uff01\u306e\u305e\u307f\u5bfe\u5bae\u7530\u306e\u63cf\u304d\u4e0b\u308d\u3057\u8907\u88fd\u539f\u753b\u30d7\u30ec\u30bc\u30f3\u30c8\u3082 |url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/230253 |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |accessdate=April 27, 2019 |language=ja |date=April 26, 2017}}</ref><ref name=end>{{Cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-21/daichi-sorayomi-ends-keijo-aquatic-sports-manga/.115127|title=Daichi Sorayomi Ends Keijo!!!!!!!! Aquatic Sports Manga|website=Anime News Network|date=April 21, 2017|accessdate=April 21, 2017|u