11-10 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225193642/https://twitter.com/plus3toogres/status/796374941922947072 |archivedate=2017-12-25 }}</ref>}}\n:Is an Elite Class Rank 2. She is a former swimmer and initially claims the title of the fastest in Western Japan which sparks a rivalry between her and Sayaka. As a former swimmer, she has a greater lung capacity which allows her to continuously move at a great speed without losing her breath for periods of time. Her favorite technique is the Butt Gattling. Whenever she participates in Keijo, her hair would stand which and takes a form similar to cat ears. This, in addition to her small frame and cat-like expressions, caused her friends to give her the nickname Rinrin. Her fighting style is Outfighter.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Yuko \u014cshima'''|\u5927\u5cf6 \u512a\u5b50|\u014cshima Yuko}}\n:{{Voiced by|Misa Kayama|Kristen McGuire<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:She's the main teacher in the West. She gives out tasks for the girls that are related to Keijo. Like hip toss with the beach ball and giving morning exercise. She has amazing speed as a test in the second episode knocking all four students off the land.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Nagisa Ujibe'''|\u6c0f\u90e8 \u51ea|Ujibe Nagisa}}\n:{{Voiced by|Mabuki And\u014d|[[Jamie Marchi]]<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:One of the first Keijo players and prize queens known as the Alluring Siren in the past. In the present, she is now a teacher in the training school Nozomi and the others attend. She was the first to recognize Nozomi's Vacuum Butt Cannon move and knows the danger of the attack as she once used it herself. Also she own the UTMs which she gives to Nozomi before giving to her elite class in preparation for the East West War. She has a rivalry with the Keijo training school's head teacher in East.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Miku Kobayakawa'''|\u5c0f\u65e9\u5ddd \u672a\u6765|Kobayakawa Miku}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Y\u014dko Hikasa]]|Dawn M. Bennett<ref name=\"dub cast\"/>}}\n:She's one of the other teacher's in the West. Although she looks blind, she's also a good Keijo teacher. She's able to hit Nozomi Kaminashi when she's not paying attention with a perfect butt hit with the chalk on her forehead.\n\n;{{Nihongo|'''Kotone Fujisaki'''|\u85e4\u5d0e \u7434\u97f3|Fujisaki Kotone}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Shizuka Ishigami]]|[[Jad Saxton]]}}\n:Is an Elite Class Rank 4. She comes from a family of Keijo players and is naturally gifted at the sport. However, she sees it as nothing more than work, until she meets Nozomi and participate in Keijo for the first time. She can attack while her back is turned and uses the vibrations on the Land to detect and predict her opponents' movements without looking. Her buttocks releases an aura that takes the form of a dog she calls Cerberus and her buttocks appear to be able to home in on her target as though she were moving on auto-pilot. When not participating in Keijo, she is always listening to homosexual stories on her headset and occasionally fantasizes about it which, to her opponents, makes it appear uninteresting. Her fighting style is Infighter.\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n''Keijo!!!!!!!!'' is written and illustrated by Daichi Sorayomi. It ran in [[Shogakukan]]'s [[sh\u014dnen manga|''sh\u014dnen'' manga]] magazine ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Sunday]]'' from July 24, 2013 to April 26, 2017,<ref>{{cite web |title=\u300c\u9280\u306e\u5319\u300d\u79d8\u8535\u8a2d\u5b9a\u96c6\u304c\u30b5\u30f3\u30c7\u30fc\u306b\u3001\u7a7a\u8a60\u5927\u667a\u65b0\u9023\u8f09\u3082 |url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/95638 |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |accessdate=April 27, 2019 |language=ja |date=July 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u300c\u7af6\u5973!!!!!!!!\u300d\u7d42\u5c3b\uff01\u306e\u305e\u307f\u5bfe\u5bae\u7530\u306e\u63cf\u304d\u4e0b\u308d\u3057\u8907\u88fd\u539f\u753b\u30d7\u30ec\u30bc\u30f3\u30c8\u3082 |url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/230253 |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |accessdate=April 27, 2019 |language=ja |date=April 26, 2017}}</ref><ref name=end>{{Cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-21/daichi-sorayomi-ends-keijo-aquatic-sports-manga/.115127|title=Daichi Sorayomi Ends Keijo!!!!!!!! Aquatic Sports Manga|website=Anime News Network|date=April 21, 2017|accessdate=April 21, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422151652/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-21/daichi-sorayomi-ends-keijo-aquatic-sports-manga/.115127|archivedate=April 22, 2017}}</ref> and was collected into eighteen ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u7af6\u5973\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\u3000\uff11\uff18 |url=https://www.shogakukan.co.jp/books/09127725 |publisher=[[Shogakukan]] |accessdate=April 27, 2019 |language=ja}}</ref>\n\n===Volume list===\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| OneLanguage  = yes\n| Language     = Japanese \n| Width        = 100%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber = 01\n | RelDate      = November 18, 2013<ref name=\"vol1\">{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u7af6\u5973\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\u3000\uff11 |url=http://www.shogakukan.co.jp/books/09124505 |publisher=[[Shogakukan]] |accessdate=March 29, 2020 |language=Japanese|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324113630/http://www.shogakukan.co.jp/books/09124505|archivedate=March 24, 2016}}</ref>\n | ISBN         = 978-4-09-124505-2\n | LicensedRelDate= \n | LicensedISBN= \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber = 02\n | RelDate      = February 18, 2014<ref name=\"vol2\">{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u7af6\u5973\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\uff01\u3000\uff12 |url=https://www.shogakukan.co.jp/books/09124565 |publisher=[[Shogakukan]] |accessdate=March 29, 2020 |language=Japanese|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810070223/https://www.shogakukan.co.jp/books/09124565|archivedate=August 10, 2019}}</ref>\n | ISBN         = 978-4-09-124565-6\n | LicensedRelDate= \n | LicensedISBN= \n}