/09110518.html |archive-date=August 22, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe anime is produced by [[Xebec (studio)|Xebec]]. It was directed by Hideya Takahashi, written by Takao Kato, composed by [[Hayato Matsuo]], and the characters designed by Keiya Nakano.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-16/keijo-tv-anime-cast-staff-revealed/.102171 |title=Keijo!!!!!!!! TV Anime's Cast, Staff Revealed |date=May 16, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=May 16, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031020233/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-16/keijo-tv-anime-cast-staff-revealed/.102171 |archive-date=October 31, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> The opening theme (from episodes 1 to 11), \"Dream X Scramble!\", was performed by Airi, while the ending theme, \"Fantas/Hip Girlfriends!\", was performed by [[Lynn (voice actress)|Lynn]], [[Mao Ichimichi|M.A.O]], [[Kaede Hondo]] and [[Saori \u014cnishi]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-12/keijo-tv-anime-new-promo-reveals-theme-song-artists/.105295 |title=Keijo!!!!!!!! TV Anime's New Promo Reveals Theme Song Artists |date=August 12, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=September 25, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031062627/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-08-12/keijo-tv-anime-new-promo-reveals-theme-song-artists/.105295 |archive-date=October 31, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> The series was released across six [[Blu-ray]] and [[DVD]] home video release volumes,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-20/keijo-tv-anime-to-have-12-episodes/.106651 |title=Keijo!!!!!!!! TV Anime to Have 12 Episodes |date=September 20, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=September 25, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031064803/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-20/keijo-tv-anime-to-have-12-episodes/.106651 |archive-date=October 31, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> and each volume includes an [[original video animation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-24/keijo-anime-home-video-releases-get-6-bonus-anime/.106709 |title=Keijo!!!!!!!! Anime's Home Video Releases Get 6 'Bonus Anime' |date=September 24, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=September 25, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031064852/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-24/keijo-anime-home-video-releases-get-6-bonus-anime/.106709 |archive-date=October 31, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> The anime is streamed by [[Crunchyroll]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-06/crunchyroll-to-stream-kiss-him-not-me-miss-bernard-said-keijo-anime/.107317 |title=Crunchyroll to Stream Kiss Him, Not Me!, Miss Bernard said., Keijo!!!!!!!! Anime (Updated) |website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=October 6, 2016 |accessdate=October 6, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106222601/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-06/crunchyroll-to-stream-kiss-him-not-me-miss-bernard-said-keijo-anime/.107317 |archive-date=November 6, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Funimation]], the latter of which streams an English dub.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-04/funimation-announces-fall-english-dub-line-up/.107252 |title=Funimation Announces Fall English Dub Line-Up |website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=October 4, 2016 |accessdate=October 4, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031065052/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-04/funimation-announces-fall-english-dub-line-up/.107252 |archive-date=October 31, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====Episode list====\n{|class=\"plainrowheaders wikitable\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF;\"\n! style=\"width:3em;\"  | No.\n!  Title{{efn|All English titles are taken from Funimation.}}\n! style=\"width:12em;\" | Original air date<ref>{{cite web|url=http://s.mxtv.jp/anime/keijollllllll/episode.php|title=\u7af6\u5973!!!!!!!!|language=Japanese|publisher=Tokyo Metropolitan Television|accessdate=December 15, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009192847/http://s.mxtv.jp/anime/keijollllllll/episode.php|archivedate=October 9, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = Setouchi Keijo Training School!!!!\n| TranslitTitle       = Setouchi Keijo Y\u014dsei Gakk\u014d!!!!\n| NativeTitle         = \u702c\u6238\u5185\u7af6\u5973\u990a\u6210\u5b66\u6821!!!!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2016|10|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nozomi partakes in try-outs at a keijo school half a year ago, alongside with the students. She stays in the game, until only she and Hanabi are left: the two fight on equal footing, but Hanabi knocks Nozomi into the water. In the present, Nozomi and Miyata pass the try-outs, and move into their dormitory room at the start of the term, where they meet Non and Kazane.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| Title               = The Hip Toss Brings Us Together!!!!\n| TranslitTitle       = Danketsu no Hippu Tosu!!!!\n| NativeTitle         = \u56e3\u7d50\u306e\u30d2\u30c3\u30d7\u30c8\u30b9!!!!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2016|10|13}}\n| ShortSummary        = The students are doing keijo exercises, one of which involves passing a beach ball around in a group, using only one's buttocks. Nozomi's team initially struggles, but Kazane accurately guides them to where the ball lands by reading the wind currents with encouragement from Nozomi. The team is placed in an evaluation match with Nagisa, one of the keijo teachers. As a sudden shock, Nozomi used the \"vacuum butt cannon\" for the first time on her team mates, leaving her speechless.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| Title               = Vacuum Butt Cannon!!!!\n| TranslitTit