ndulum then knocks them out with her breast, resulting in a win.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 5\n| Title               = Full-Auto Cerberus!!!!\n| TranslitTitle       = Jid\u014d geigeki (furu\u014dto) keruberosu!!!!\n| NativeTitle         = \u81ea\u52d5\u8fce\u6483\uff08\u30d5\u30eb\u30aa\u30fc\u30c8\uff09\u30b1\u30eb\u30d9\u30ed\u30b9!!!!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2016|11|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nozomi faces Kotone in the class-change race, who dodges all attacks while having her back turned, knocked two opponents away and chases Nozomi using Cerberus, a move where a ghostly image of a dog is manifested from her buttocks. The two collide, and Nozomi wins in a battle of power. After Nagisa checks Nozomi's butt condition, she allows her to learn the move and advise her to take her courses more seriously, despite not asking Nagisa for permission to use the move. Nozomi and her roommates all advance to the elite class; Kazane, despite losing, had performed well and cornered Mio, which was why Mio was forced to use hypnosis, a move she was banned from using.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 6\n| Title               = Alluring Kyoto Trip!!!!\n| TranslitTitle       = Miwaku no Ky\u014dto gasshuku!!!!\n| NativeTitle         = \u9b45\u60d1\u306e\u4eac\u90fd\u5408\u5bbf!!!!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2016|11|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = The elite class goes on a field trip to Kyoto, where they are divided into groups based on their fighting styles. There they meet the professional Keijo players after a three hour chance to look around the city. Also Mio's mysterious friend is unhappy of Nozomi's friendship with Mio.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 7\n| Title               = Where the Turnips Lead!!!!\n| TranslitTitle       = Kabu no michibiku saki!!!!\n| NativeTitle         = \u30ab\u30d6\u306e\u5c0e\u304f\u5148!!!!\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| 