imulcasts-for-u.s-canada/.108362 |archive-date=November 4, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2017, fans in Portugal were in the planning stages for a defictionalized Keijo sport league. The rules of the defictionalized version were modified and protective gear for the breasts, rear, and thighs were added to make the sport \"safer and more realistic\". A proof of concept video showed a match in action and the league planned to scout for interested parties and venues for play.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/07/22/you-can-stop-wishing-keijo-is-now-a-real-sport|title=You Can Stop Wishing: \"Keijo!!!!!!!!\" Is Now a Real Sport|work=Crunchyroll|access-date=2017-07-23|language=en|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723143603/http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2017/07/22/you-can-stop-wishing-keijo-is-now-a-real-sport|archivedate=2017-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://otakomu.jp/archives/575537.html|title=\u300e\u7af6\u5973!!!!!!!!\u300f\u304c\u6d77\u5916\u304b\u3089\u300c\u7af6\u5973\u3092\u672c\u5f53\u306e\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u7af6\u6280\u306b\u3057\u306a\u3044\u304b\uff1f\u300d\u3068\u63d0\u6848\u3055\u308c\u305f\u3053\u3068\u304c\u5224\u660e\uff01\u6d77\u5916\u4eba\u6c17\u51c4\u3059\u304e\uff57\uff57\uff57 {{!}} \u30aa\u30bf\u30af.com|website=otakomu.jp|language=ja|access-date=2017-07-23|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170929063746/http://otakomu.jp/archives/575537.html|archivedate=2017-09-29}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://websunday.net/rensai/keijo/|Official manga website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Official website|http://keijollllllll.com/|Official anime website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|manga|18056|title=Keijo!!!!!!!!}}\n\n{{Weekly Sh\u014dnen Sunday - 2010\u20132019}}\n{{Xebec}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Keijo}}\n[[Category:2013 manga]]\n[[Category:Anime series based on manga]]\n[[Category:Bandai Namco 